Turkish and Turkmen of Iraq: `apertium-tur-tki`
===============================================================================

This is an Apertium language pair for translating between Turkish and
Turkmen of Iraq. What you can use this language package for:

* Translating between Turkish and Turkmen of Iraq
* Morphological analysis of Turkish and Turkmen of Iraq
* Part-of-speech tagging of Turkish and Turkmen of Iraq

For information on the latter two points, see subheading "For more
information" below.

Requirements
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

You will need the following software installed:

* lttoolbox (>= 3.3.0)
* apertium (>= 3.3.0)
* vislcg3 (>= 0.9.9.10297)
* apertium-tur
* apertium-tki

If this does not make any sense, we recommend you look at: www.apertium.org.

Compiling
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Given the requirements being installed, you should be able to just run:

```console
$ ./configure
$ make
# make install
```

You can use `./autogen.sh` instead of `./configure` in case you're compiling
from source. If you installed any prerequisite language packages using a
`--prefix` with `./configure`, make sure to use the same `--prefix` when running
`./configure` here.

Testing
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

If you are in the source directory after running make, the following
commands should work:

```console
$ echo "TODO test sentence 1" | apertium -d . tur-tki
TODO test translated sentence 1

$ echo "TODO test sentence 2" | apertium -d . tki-tur
TODO test translated sentence 2
```

After installing somewhere in `$PATH`, you should be able to do e.g.

```console
$ echo "TODO test sentence 1" | apertium tur-tki
TODO test translated sentence 1
```

Files and data
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

* [`apertium-tur-tki.tur-tki.dix`](apertium-tur-tki.tur-tki.dix) - Bilingual dictionary
* [`apertium-tur-tki.tur-tki.t1x`](apertium-tur-tki.tur-tki.t1x) - Chunking rules for translating into Turkmen of Iraq
* [`apertium-tur-tki.tki-tur.t1x`](apertium-tur-tki.tki-tur.t1x) - Chunking rules for translating into Turkish
* [`apertium-tur-tki.tur-tki.t2x`](apertium-tur-tki.tur-tki.t2x) - Interchunk rules for translating into Turkmen of Iraq
* [`apertium-tur-tki.tki-tur.t2x`](apertium-tur-tki.tki-tur.t2x) - Interchunk rules for translating into Turkish
* [`apertium-tur-tki.tur-tki.t3x`](apertium-tur-tki.tur-tki.t3x) - Postchunk rules for translating into Turkmen of Iraq
* [`apertium-tur-tki.tki-tur.t3x`](apertium-tur-tki.tki-tur.t3x) - Postchunk rules for translating into Turkish
* [`apertium-tur-tki.tur-tki.lrx`](apertium-tur-tki.tur-tki.lrx) - Lexical selection rules for translating into Turkmen of Iraq
* [`apertium-tur-tki.tki-tur.lrx`](apertium-tur-tki.tki-tur.lrx) - Lexical selection rules for translating into Turkish
* [`modes.xml`](modes.xml) - Translation modes

